COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. Hilda H. GERSTLE et al. No. 8904. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 29, 1938. James W. Morris, Asst. U. S. Atty. Gen., for petitioner. Francis W. Murphy, of San Francisco, Cal., for respondents.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of motion of counsel for petitioner, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered petitions to review herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
